cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper deals with security and privacy issues in web browsing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of trusted hardware enclaves also suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses UI considerations, which could relate to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the implementation and evaluation of the system could involve distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
